					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The Y scroll increment happen somewhere (I think cycle 250 if Nintendulator's source says so it should be right), no matter if you write to $2006 or not.<br />1)<br />There is 2 ways to correctly set the Y scroll...<br />Either you write the fine scroll Y-1 before the cycle 250, or you write the fine scroll Y after cycle 250. In both cases you have to make sure the jittering will never make your 2nd $2006 write before/after 250 else you'll have a shaking image.<br /><br />2)<br />The fine X scroll takes effect immediately. You could modify it as many times you want in a scanline. It's just not practical because of jittering, so this is why few (if any) games or tech demoes ever did this.<br /><br />3)<br />You can do scroll writes anytimes really. There is nothing preventing you to execute a &quot;sta $2005&quot; or &quot;sta $2006&quot; instruction no matter where the PPU is in it's fame. Glitches are hard to avoid because of jittering (once again...) But normally you can avoid them it's just it requires patience and trial-and-error testing.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

